CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 21, 1961, pg. 29, reads: "Schenley Spartans - This is the Schenley team that will be trying to knock Westinghouse out of contention for Section 1 honors, in city championship race, on Friday. Left to right, front row: Kennard Williams, end; Francis Peay, tackle; Howard Woods, guard, who is substituting for regular Louis McTurner; Donald Colaizzi, center; Ronald Washington, guard; Norgon Anderson, tackle, and Donald Turner, end.  Back row; Ronald Porter, halfback; Neal Ramsey, quarterback; Adolphus Banks, fullback, and John Bailey, halfback. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Schenley High School football team, front row from left: Kennard Williams, Francis Peay, Howard Woods, Donald Colaizzi, Ronald Washington, Norgon Anderson, and Donald Turner; back row: Ronald Porter, Neal Ramsey, Adolphus Banks, and John Bailey, in formation on field, another version
